{"_id":"ODE0ODYwM2RjMWZi","name":"Tan Bag of Tricks","content":"<h4>Tan Bag of Tricks</h4><p><i>Wondrous item, uncommon</i></p><p>This ordinary bag, made from tan cloth, appears empty. Reaching inside the bag, however, reveals the presence of a small, fuzzy object. The bag weighs 1/2 pound.</p><p>You can use an action to pull the fuzzy object from the bag and throw it up to 20 feet. When the object lands, it transforms into a creature you determine by rolling a d8 and consulting the table that corresponds to the bag's color.</p><p>The creature is friendly to you and your companions, and it acts on your turn. You can use a bonus action to command how the creature moves and what action it takes on its next turn, or to give it general orders, such as to attack your enemies. In the absence of such orders, the creature acts in a fashion appropriate to its nature.</p><p>Once three fuzzy objects have been pulled from the bag, the bag can't be used again until the next dawn.</p><table class=\"userscript-table userscript-table-bordered\"><thead><tr><th>d8</th><th>Creature</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>1</td><td>@Actor[YzVkODYwMmY2ZjFi]{Jackal}</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td>@Actor[Y2NjOTQwNjNkYTdk]{Ape}</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td>@Actor[MjViZGE4ZWY3OTZl]{Baboon}</td></tr><tr><td>4</td><td>@Actor[NWRiNGVhMzgxOGFl]{Axe beak}</td></tr><tr><td>5</td><td>@Actor[NzE4MTViZjNhMTZm]{Black bear}</td></tr><tr><td>6</td><td>@Actor[N2ExOWMyOWM3MTA4]{Giant weasel}</td></tr><tr><td>7</td><td>@Actor[NTE2YmJjNDkwMDM0]{Giant hyena}</td></tr><tr><td>8</td><td>@Actor[MDdiMjMzYjUzNmU4]{Tiger}</td></tr></tbody></table>","img":"worlds/cor-gos/journal/002_-_Magic_Items/030_-_Tan_Bag_of_Tricks/avatar.webp","folder":"ODU3ZmEyODkxOTk5","sort":300000,"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":30,"handout-archived":false}}}
{"_id":"ODI3ODY3M2U0MTU3","name":"Lizardfolk Roster","content":"<section class=\"secret\"><p>GM Notes : </p><h2>Lizardfolk Roster</h2><h3>Area 2</h3><ul><li><b>Occupants at Start:</b> 5 @Actor[YjM2YzY3ODkxYzU3]{lizardfolk}</li><li><b>Notes:</b> These guards are alerted by noise in 1. If they are challenged, one of the guards tries to escape to 3 for help.</li></ul><hr /><h3>Area 3</h3><ul><li><b>Occupants at Start:</b> 3 @Actor[YjM2YzY3ODkxYzU3]{lizardfolk}, 1 @Actor[OTU5MDgyOGNjN2U1]{lizardfolk scaleshield}<br /></li><li><b>Notes: </b>If a guard from 2 escaped, these guards go to 2. If not, they remain here until alerted by noise nearby.</li></ul><hr /><h3>Area 5</h3><ul><li><b>Occupants at Start:</b> 1 @Actor[OTU5MDgyOGNjN2U1]{lizardfolk scaleshield}</li><li><b>Notes:</b> This officer is alerted by noise in 3. The guards in 2 and 3, if they are still present, join the officer in this room when they hear sounds of battle.</li></ul><hr /><h3>Area 7</h3><ul><li><b>Occupants at Start:</b> 5 @Actor[ZjUxNjUzYzU1MWY4]{lizardfolk commoner}s</li><li><b>Notes:</b> The kitchen workers escape to 9 if allowed to do so.</li></ul><hr /><h3>Area 9</h3><ul><li><b>Occupants at Start:</b> 4 @Actor[YjM2YzY3ODkxYzU3]{lizardfolk}, 1 @Actor[OTU5MDgyOGNjN2U1]{lizardfolk scaleshield}, 1 @Actor[ODQzMjFjMTQ4NGEy]{lizardfolk shaman}</li><li><b>Notes:</b> These guards go to 7 if a commoner escapes to warn them of the characters in that room. Otherwise they remain here.</li></ul><hr /><h3>Area 10</h3><ul><li><b>Occupants at Start:</b> 5 @Actor[ZjUxNjUzYzU1MWY4]{lizardfolk commoner}s</li><li><b>Notes:</b> The banquet workers escape to 29 if allowed to do so. The characters might accompany them.</li></ul><hr /><h3>Area 11</h3><ul><li><b>Occupants at Start:</b> 2 hatchlings</li><li><b>Notes:</b> Friendly hatchlings (noncombatants) latch onto the characters if they’re not discouraged from doing so.</li></ul><hr /><h3>Area 12</h3><ul><li><b>Occupants at Start:</b> 2 @Actor[MzIzMjkwZDkxNmRl]{amphisbaenae}, 1 @Actor[ODQzMjFjMTQ4NGEy]{lizardfolk shaman}</li><li><b>Notes:</b> The shaman tries to flee to the west. If it does so, it races to 20 looking for help.</li></ul><hr /><h3>Area 20</h3><ul><li><b>Occupants at Start:</b> 2 @Actor[YjM2YzY3ODkxYzU3]{lizardfolk}, 1 @Actor[ODQzMjFjMTQ4NGEy]{lizardfolk shaman}</li><li><b>Notes:</b> These lizardfolk go to 12, responding to the threat if alerted by the shaman that escaped from that area.</li></ul><hr /><h3>Area 22</h3><ul><li><b>Occupants at Start:</b> 6 @Actor[MjQ1ZDBhNzI4MmFm]{giant lizards}</li><li><b>Notes:</b> The giant lizards remain here until encountered. No amount of noise or disruption will coax the reptiles elsewhere.</li></ul><hr /><h3>Area 23</h3><ul><li><b>Occupants at Start:</b> 3 @Actor[YjM2YzY3ODkxYzU3]{lizardfolk}</li><li><b>Notes:</b> These lizardfolk go to 22 if alerted by sounds of combat there. They go to 24 if a commoner escapes from that room and arrives here.</li></ul><hr /><h3>Area 24</h3><ul><li><b>Occupants at Start:</b> 20 @Actor[ZjUxNjUzYzU1MWY4]{lizardfolk commoner}s, 13 hatchlings</li><li><b>Notes:</b> These lizardfolk protect hatchlings (noncombatants) and guard the entrance to 25. If combat starts, two commoners try to flee to 23 and get help.</li></ul><hr /><h3>Area 25</h3><ul><li><b>Occupants at Start:</b> 3 hatchlings</li><li><b>Notes:</b> The hatchlings (noncombatants) remain here.</li></ul><hr /><h3>Area 26</h3><ul><li><b>Occupants at Start:</b> 5 @Actor[OGU3MTBlM2I5OTIz]{giant poisonous snakes} </li><li><b>Notes:</b> The snakes remain here.</li></ul><hr /><h3>Area 27</h3><ul><li><b>Occupants at Start:</b> 1 @Actor[YjM2YzY3ODkxYzU3]{lizardfolk}, 1 @Actor[NDM0NDJlMmJlODQy]{lizardfolk render}</li><li><b>Notes:</b> These lizardfolk move toward the gate if alerted by noise in that area. Otherwise they remain here.</li></ul><hr /><h3>Area 29</h3><ul><li><b>Occupants at Start: </b>4 @Actor[YjM2YzY3ODkxYzU3]{lizardfolk}, 1 @Actor[NDM0NDJlMmJlODQy]{lizardfolk render}, 1 @Actor[OTU5MDgyOGNjN2U1]{lizardfolk scaleshield}</li><li><b>Notes:</b> These lizardfolk go to 10 if a commoner escapes to warn them of the characters in that room. Otherwise they remain here.</li></ul><hr /><h3>Area 32</h3><ul><li><b>Occupants at Start: </b>3 @Actor[YjM2YzY3ODkxYzU3]{lizardfolk}, 1 @Actor[OTU5MDgyOGNjN2U1]{lizardfolk scaleshield}</li><li><b>Notes:</b> These lizardfolk remain here until encountered.</li></ul><hr /><h3>Area 35</h3><ul><li><b>Occupants at Start: </b>2 @Actor[ZjUxNjUzYzU1MWY4]{lizardfolk commoner}s</li><li><b>Notes:</b> These commoners try to flee to 36 if attacked.</li></ul><hr /><h3>Area 38</h3><ul><li><b>Occupants at Start:</b> @Actor[NGEyZmVmNzE1MmEz]{Sauriv} (lizardfolk noble)</li><li><b>Notes:</b> The minister (noncombatant) remains here unless the characters fail to win his favor. If that happens, he tries to flee to 40.</li></ul><hr /><h3>Area 40</h3><ul><li><b>Occupants at Start: </b>1 @Actor[ZmQ1MzE2NjU1Mzky]{lizard queen}, 1 @Actor[ZDBmODU5MDQ3Nzc0]{lizardfolk subchief}, 2 @Actor[OTU5MDgyOGNjN2U1]{lizardfolk scaleshield}s, 1 @Actor[NDM0NDJlMmJlODQy]{lizardfolk render}, 8 @Actor[YjM2YzY3ODkxYzU3]{lizardfolk}</li><li><b>Notes:</b> These lizardfolk remain here until encountered, unwilling to jeopardize the queen’s defense by leaving.</li></ul><hr /><h3>Area 42</h3><ul><li><b>Occupants at Start: </b>3 @Actor[YjM2YzY3ODkxYzU3]{lizardfolk}, 1 @Actor[OTU5MDgyOGNjN2U1]{lizardfolk scaleshield}</li><li><b>Notes:</b> These guards go to the gate at 41 (north) in response to noise there. Otherwise they remain here until encountered. If that happens, one tries to flee to 44 to get reinforcements.</li></ul><hr /><h3>Area 43a</h3><ul><li><b>Occupants at Start: </b>1 @Actor[MzIxNmM4MzI1NmVk]{sahuagin}</li><li><b>Notes:</b> The sahuagin remains here unless the characters release it.</li></ul><hr /><h3>Area 43e</h3><ul><li><b>Occupants at Start: </b>1 @Actor[ZjUxNjUzYzU1MWY4]{lizardfolk commoner}</li><li><b>Notes:</b> The commoner remains here unless the characters release it. If that happens, it tries to flee to 44.</li></ul><hr /><h3>Area 44</h3><ul><li><b>Occupants at Start: </b>2 @Actor[YjM2YzY3ODkxYzU3]{lizardfolk}, 1 @Actor[OTU5MDgyOGNjN2U1]{lizardfolk scaleshield}</li><li><b>Notes:</b> These guards go to 42, 48, or 52 if alerted to the presence of characters in those areas. Otherwise they remain here until encountered.</li></ul><hr /><h3>Area 48</h3><ul><li><b>Occupants at Start: </b>4 @Actor[YjM2YzY3ODkxYzU3]{lizardfolk}</li><li><b>Notes:</b> These guards go to the gate at 41 (south) in response to noise there. If they hear sounds of combat in 52, three go there and one goes to 44 for added help.</li></ul><hr /><h3>Area 49</h3><ul><li><b>Occupants at Start: </b>4 @Actor[YjM2YzY3ODkxYzU3]{lizardfolk}</li><li><b>Notes:</b> If these lizardfolk become aware of intruders, one goes to 42 and elsewhere looking for reinforcements. Another one goes to 50, 51, and 52 in succession to alert the occupants there.</li></ul><hr /><h3>Area 50</h3><ul><li><b>Occupants at Start: </b>3 @Actor[YmZmNjYxMTExMjZj]{koalinth}, 1 @Actor[Y2ExYWQ1ZWRkMWYx]{koalinth sergeant}</li><li><b>Notes:</b> The koalinth go to 49 if alerted to the presence of intruders there, eager to support their lizardfolk allies.</li></ul><hr /><h3>Area 51</h3><ul><li><b>Occupants at Start: </b>4 @Actor[MzQ5ZmVhNjU5Nzc2]{locathah}, 1 @Actor[ZmFlM2FjYWUxOGVi]{locathah hunter}, 5 @Actor[NmYyNzQyZWRkYzMx]{giant sea eels}</li><li><b>Notes:</b> The locathah and their eels go to 49 if alerted to the presence of intruders there.</li></ul><hr /><h3>Area 52</h3><ul><li><b>Occupants at Start: </b>3 @Actor[ZGRkN2Y2MzdhMzZl]{merfolk}, 1 @Actor[NDcwZWI4MjhjZWQz]{merfolk salvager}</li><li><b>Notes:</b> The merfolk go to 49 if alerted to the presence of intruders there, cooperating with their allies.</li></ul></section>","img":null,"folder":"YTZlODg5MDc3Nzkx","sort":40000,"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":4,"handout-archived":false}}}
